The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Ericsson, Nokia bag BSNL deal

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Sept. 7: Bharat Sanchar Nigam (BSNL) has awarded its $1.3-billion network contract to global equipment companies Ericsson and Nokia-Siemens. The contract will enable the public sector unit to add 22.75 million GSM lines on its network.

 BSNLs new chairman and managing director Kuldeep Goyal also said the company generated revenue of Rs 39,715 crore and a net profit of Rs 7,806 crore in 2006-07. 

 We will invest Rs 22,880 crore this fiscal to expand telecom services, Goyal added. 

 The contract will see BSNL adding about two million connections a month from next year. Swedish telecom company Ericsson, which will lay 13.12 million lines, has accepted the letter of intent. 

 An intent letter will be mailed to Nokia-Siemens, which will set up the infrastructure for 9.675 million GSM lines. 




